    <div class="narrative">
      <p>Beyond the Citadel, in the most remote mountains of the realm, stand the Titan's Forges - gigantic workshops carved into volcanic rock. Here, artisans work on artifacts so massive that no ordinary scroll could contain them: enchanted armor, maps of entire worlds, three-dimensional models of cathedrals.</p>
      <p>The Master Blacksmith greets you with a grunt. His hands are covered in soot and runes.</p>
      <p>"Standard chronicles are made for text - words, incantations, formulas. But here, we work with <strong>massive artifacts</strong>. Textures, 3D models, sounds, animations. If you try to archive them like ordinary text, <strong>your chronicles will explode in size</strong> and become unusable. You need a special tool. You need <strong>the Titan's Forges</strong>."</p>
    </div>

